<tr>
<td align=center colspan = 2>
<font size=3>
<br>
In my project I am trying to change the color of the light that illuminates the foreground subject in the image. The liht illuminated area is first identified by clustering the colors. A control point input is taken from the user via cmd line. The control point will determine which part of the image to be illuminated with a different color. 
<br><br>In the following images, I'm trying to replace the white white-light illuminated subject(my face) with a different coloured-light illuminated subject in a smooth way <br><br>
To run code: ./pr10 special image.ppm threshold control_point_X control_point_Y <br>
Example: ./pr10 special ash.ppm 10 315 250
 </td>
</tr>

